WEBVTT

00:02.278 --> 00:04.625
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:21.987 --> 00:26.095
â™ªâ™ª

00:26.129 --> 00:27.579
Gumball:
I don't know, dude.

00:27.613 --> 00:29.719
I just don't think this
camouflage is working.

00:29.753 --> 00:31.928
And it's getting
really hot in this.

00:32.653 --> 00:34.379
What?
I thought it might snow.

00:34.413 --> 00:35.380
It's June.

00:35.414 --> 00:36.691
Why are we
doing this, anyway?

00:36.726 --> 00:38.245
Because it's getting
embarrassing.

00:38.279 --> 00:39.694
We keep bumping
into our neighbor,

00:39.729 --> 00:41.213
and we don't even
know his name.

00:41.248 --> 00:43.112
-Mr. Robinson?
-No, the other one.

00:43.146 --> 00:44.630
Mrs. Robinson?

00:44.665 --> 00:46.805
No, the guy who lives
on the other side.

00:46.839 --> 00:48.186
You know...

00:48.220 --> 00:51.465
A really small person
playing a normal-sized piano?

00:51.499 --> 00:54.088
A normal-sized person
playing a really tall piano?

00:54.123 --> 00:58.713
Someone, uh, tickling --
the sky tickler!

00:58.748 --> 01:00.060
No! Him.

01:00.094 --> 01:01.751
Oh, yeah.

01:01.785 --> 01:03.097
No, I don't know
that guy's name.

01:03.132 --> 01:04.581
Exactly.
We don't know it,

01:04.616 --> 01:06.825
and we're running out of ways
to get away with it.

01:06.859 --> 01:08.896
Hey, Gumball, Darwin.

01:08.930 --> 01:11.623
Hello...sir.

01:11.864 --> 01:14.004
Come on now,
I've known you for years.

01:14.039 --> 01:15.592
You don't need
to call me "sir."

01:15.627 --> 01:16.800
You can call me by name.

01:21.288 --> 01:22.565
Yes, we can.

01:22.599 --> 01:25.809
And we will
definitely do that.

01:25.844 --> 01:28.433
Next time.

01:28.467 --> 01:29.468
[ Bell dinging ]

01:29.503 --> 01:31.815
Oh, gosh darn it.

01:31.850 --> 01:33.921
[ Train whistle blows ][ Gasps ]

01:33.955 --> 01:37.994
Look out, Mr. -- Uh,
Mr. -- Mr., uh --

01:38.028 --> 01:40.445
Mr...

01:40.479 --> 01:42.171
Mr. Mister?

01:42.205 --> 01:43.448
Mister?

01:43.482 --> 01:44.690
Mister.

01:44.725 --> 01:46.140
Man, I wish I knew his --

01:46.175 --> 01:48.246
[ Splat! ]
[ Gasps ]

01:48.280 --> 01:49.971
We better call him
the paramedics.

01:50.006 --> 01:51.145
Why?
I'm pretty sure

01:51.180 --> 01:52.526
The Paramedics
is not his name.

01:52.560 --> 01:54.010
No, I mean,
call a doctor.

01:54.044 --> 01:55.253
Nah, it'll only be awkward

01:55.287 --> 01:56.875
when they ask us
what he's called.

01:56.909 --> 01:57.979
[ Door opens ]

01:58.014 --> 01:59.291
Nigel: And here to talk
about his job

01:59.326 --> 02:00.706
is the town's mailman, Mr...

02:00.741 --> 02:01.811
[ Both gasp ]

02:01.845 --> 02:02.674
[ Glass breaking ]

02:02.708 --> 02:04.814
Maybe we should
have waited.

02:04.848 --> 02:07.368
Principal Brown was about
to tell us his name.

02:07.403 --> 02:08.956
Yup.
I panicked.

02:08.990 --> 02:10.440
Yeah, remember this time?

02:10.475 --> 02:12.132
This was really awkward.

02:12.166 --> 02:13.857
This isn't a flashback.

02:13.892 --> 02:15.342
[ Whoosh! ]

02:15.376 --> 02:17.171
Wait up!
I've got a package for you!

02:17.206 --> 02:18.276
[ Door slams ]

02:18.310 --> 02:19.449
[ Both panting ]

02:19.484 --> 02:20.726
We can't avoid it
any longer.

02:20.761 --> 02:22.487
We're gonna have to
ask him his name.

02:22.521 --> 02:23.798
Are you insane?

02:23.833 --> 02:25.006
You're forgetting
about the window.

02:25.041 --> 02:26.318
Unh-unh.

02:26.353 --> 02:27.630
I am not jumping
through any more windows.

02:27.664 --> 02:29.321
I'm still finding
bits of window frame

02:29.356 --> 02:31.012
in my gills from
the last time.

02:31.047 --> 02:32.842
No, I'm talking about the brief
window of opportunity

02:32.876 --> 02:34.326
where it's socially
acceptable

02:34.361 --> 02:35.707
to ask someone what
their name is.

02:35.741 --> 02:37.329
After the third time
you've met someone,

02:37.364 --> 02:38.675
that window closes.

02:38.710 --> 02:40.367
And every time you see them
after that,

02:40.401 --> 02:41.747
the window gets another
lock on it,

02:41.782 --> 02:43.197
another bolt,
another shutter.

02:43.232 --> 02:44.854
At this point, our window
with that guy

02:44.888 --> 02:47.028
would be harder to open
than a ski store in the Sahara.

02:47.063 --> 02:48.202
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:48.237 --> 02:49.376
Neighbor:
What about your package?

02:49.410 --> 02:50.687
What's he trying
to deliver, anyway?

02:50.722 --> 02:52.033
Dad:
It's probably for me.

02:52.068 --> 02:53.656
I don't know that
guy's name, either.

02:53.690 --> 02:55.865
I've just been avoiding him
by not leaving the house

02:55.899 --> 02:57.522
and getting everything
delivered.

02:57.556 --> 02:59.386
But isn't he the mailman?

02:59.420 --> 03:00.525
I didn't think
it through.

03:00.559 --> 03:01.767
And what's
with the jars?

03:01.802 --> 03:03.113
You don't have to
leave the house

03:03.148 --> 03:04.253
to go to the bathroom.

03:04.287 --> 03:05.495
Didn't think that through,
either.

03:05.530 --> 03:07.117
Right.
We need to find out his name

03:07.152 --> 03:08.395
without him realizing.

03:09.292 --> 03:12.192
-Hey, Gumball.
-Hello, Mr...

03:12.226 --> 03:13.572
Okay, Gumball, just keep going

03:13.607 --> 03:16.334
until you see a look
of recognition on his face.

03:16.368 --> 03:27.552
Smithbryanpetersayn
brwisestevensondavid?

03:27.655 --> 03:28.449
[ Laughs ]

03:28.484 --> 03:29.933
I'm so sorry
about my friend,

03:29.968 --> 03:33.351
Mr., uhh, manflay --

03:33.385 --> 03:35.353
I guess I'll just leave it
with the others.

03:35.387 --> 03:39.080
[ Both muttering ]

03:42.014 --> 03:43.395
[ Insects chirping ]

03:43.430 --> 03:45.432
Isn't it illegal to go
through someone's mail?

03:45.466 --> 03:47.468
What's worse,
being locked in a prison,

03:47.503 --> 03:50.160
or being locked in a prison
of social awkwardness?

03:50.195 --> 03:52.162
Jackpot!

03:52.197 --> 03:53.750
Isn't it weird
that a mailman

03:53.785 --> 03:55.821
leaves mail
in his own mailbox?

03:55.856 --> 03:57.098
I guess some people

03:57.133 --> 03:58.410
don't like to take their
work home with them.

03:58.445 --> 04:00.101
"To the occupant."
"To whom it may concern."

04:00.136 --> 04:01.551
"To the resident."
"To the homeowner."

04:01.586 --> 04:03.312
"To the billpayer."
"For your attention."

04:03.346 --> 04:04.623
"Sir or madam."
"Madam or sir."

04:04.658 --> 04:06.246
"To the birthday boy!"
Ah, come on!

04:06.280 --> 04:07.281
[ Paper shredder humming ]

04:07.316 --> 04:08.834
What are you doing?!

04:08.869 --> 04:10.250
Destroying the evidence.

04:10.284 --> 04:11.665
But we could've just put them
back in the mailbox!

04:11.699 --> 04:14.254
Good idea.

04:14.288 --> 04:16.014
[ Clanking ]

04:16.048 --> 04:19.914
[ Grunts ]

04:19.949 --> 04:21.502
The perfect crime.

04:24.540 --> 04:26.852
Excuse me, would you like
to sign our petition?

04:26.887 --> 04:29.130
Uh, I'm sorry I don't
have time to --

04:29.165 --> 04:30.649
Whoa!

04:30.684 --> 04:32.202
Thank you for stopping.
Please sign here.

04:32.237 --> 04:33.480
Um, I don't really --

04:33.514 --> 04:35.136
Great! If you could just
write your name.

04:35.171 --> 04:36.310
Full name please,
nice and clear,

04:36.345 --> 04:37.622
block capitals,
big as you can.

04:37.656 --> 04:38.968
What's it for?

04:39.002 --> 04:41.315
The Mayor's gonna knock down
the library to build a...

04:41.350 --> 04:42.420
A hospital!

04:42.454 --> 04:44.663
Oh, that doesn't
sound so bad.

04:44.698 --> 04:47.148
Yeah, but then he's gonna
knock down the hospital

04:47.183 --> 04:48.702
to build a...
-An orphanage.

04:48.736 --> 04:49.875
Again, not so bad.

04:49.910 --> 04:52.153
But then he's gonna knock
down the orphanage

04:52.188 --> 04:54.121
and build, uh,
luxury apartments!

04:54.155 --> 04:55.225
Luxury apartments.

04:55.260 --> 04:57.227
That's terrible!
Gimme me that!

04:57.262 --> 04:58.505
[ Pen clicks ]

04:58.539 --> 04:59.678
No, wait.

04:59.713 --> 05:01.059
We need direct action,
and we need it now.

05:01.093 --> 05:03.544
-Ugh!
-[ Sighs ]

05:06.754 --> 05:09.067
It's the Mayor, here.
I've got an idea.

05:09.101 --> 05:12.519
We're gonna knock down the
library and build a hospital.

05:12.553 --> 05:14.314
No, no, that's just step one.

05:14.348 --> 05:16.971
[ Pigeons cooing ]

05:17.006 --> 05:18.076
Morning.

05:18.110 --> 05:20.043
[ Grunts ]

05:20.078 --> 05:21.459
Hey!
-What the --?!

05:21.493 --> 05:23.771
[ Romantic music playing ]

05:29.915 --> 05:32.332
[ Both chewing ]

05:32.366 --> 05:33.988
[ Glass shatters ]

05:34.023 --> 05:37.026
[ Ding! ]

05:37.060 --> 05:39.580
[ Bling! ]

05:39.615 --> 05:41.064
Hey!

05:41.099 --> 05:42.100
Huh?

05:42.134 --> 05:45.068
Ugh!

05:45.103 --> 05:46.173
[ Wedding march plays ]

05:46.207 --> 05:47.830
Okay, wedding vows.
Go!

05:47.864 --> 05:51.281
Uh, I hereby state that I,
Alison Sandra Gator,

05:51.316 --> 05:53.525
do take you as
my lawful wedded husband.

05:53.560 --> 05:54.768
Okay, your turn, go!

05:54.802 --> 05:57.943
Uh, I hereby state
that I...

05:57.978 --> 05:59.117
Yes?

05:59.151 --> 06:00.877
-I...
-Yes?!

06:00.912 --> 06:02.845
-I...
-Yes!

06:02.879 --> 06:04.950
I think this is all
happening too fast!

06:04.985 --> 06:08.506
Gosh darn it!

06:08.540 --> 06:10.749
People say you're meant
to mourn a relationship

06:10.784 --> 06:13.200
for half the amount of time
you were together.

06:13.234 --> 06:15.789
I'm done.

06:19.275 --> 06:20.759
[ Doorbell rings ]

06:20.794 --> 06:22.071
Package delivery!

06:22.105 --> 06:23.383
-Sign here.
-What?

06:23.417 --> 06:25.799
But I'm the mailman
for this neighborhood!

06:25.833 --> 06:28.629
Why didn't anybody tell me
I'd been replaced?

06:28.664 --> 06:31.218
[ Sobs ] Decades
of experience, worthless!

06:31.252 --> 06:33.393
Thrown on the scrap heap
like garbage.

06:33.427 --> 06:34.877
Yeah,
if you could just --

06:34.911 --> 06:37.431
How am I gonna find
another job at my age?

06:37.466 --> 06:39.260
If you could just sign here.

06:39.295 --> 06:40.641
[ Sobbing ]

06:44.369 --> 06:45.819
Did we get it?

06:45.853 --> 06:47.786
Nope, nothing makes
handwriting harder

06:47.821 --> 06:49.547
to read than
an old man's tears.

06:49.581 --> 06:52.998
And I've already got
one of these!

06:53.033 --> 06:54.344
[ Sobbing ]

06:54.379 --> 06:55.725
[ Door closes ]

06:55.760 --> 06:57.762
There must be something
we haven't tried.

06:57.796 --> 07:00.109
I've been braining so hard,
my think hurts.

07:00.143 --> 07:01.662
Wait! I know!
If we had amnesia,

07:01.697 --> 07:03.664
we could tell him
we've forgotten his name,

07:03.699 --> 07:05.355
and it wouldn't
be embarrassing.

07:05.390 --> 07:06.909
Great!
How do you get amnesia?

07:06.943 --> 07:08.566
We hit each
other on the head.

07:08.600 --> 07:10.499
Wait, how are we gonna remember
that we tried this?

07:10.533 --> 07:13.433
Write it on your arm.

07:13.467 --> 07:14.986
Huh, that explains
the headache.

07:15.020 --> 07:18.955
Man: [ Russian accent ]
Hey, you two.

07:18.990 --> 07:20.198
That guy on your poster...

07:20.232 --> 07:21.510
Do you know his name?

07:21.544 --> 07:24.547
Let's just say
he's an old friend.

07:26.238 --> 07:28.517
[ Mailbox door creaks ]

07:28.551 --> 07:29.483
Aah!

07:29.518 --> 07:31.485
Both:
Hello, Harry Gedges!

07:31.520 --> 07:32.797
Who told you
that was my name?

07:32.831 --> 07:34.281
Pfft,
we've always known it.

07:34.315 --> 07:35.627
Obviously.

07:35.662 --> 07:36.870
Who told you that name?!

07:36.904 --> 07:38.216
Uh, those guys.

07:38.250 --> 07:40.701
[ Gasps ]
They've found me.

07:40.736 --> 07:42.669
I don't know how,
but they've found me.

07:48.433 --> 07:51.332
Wait! What's wrong with calling
you Harry Gedges, Harry Gedges?

07:51.367 --> 07:52.782
Because
that's my real name!

07:52.817 --> 07:54.888
Yeah, we know it is,
Harry Gedges!

07:54.922 --> 07:56.372
Aah!
I don't mind.

07:56.406 --> 07:58.236
Darwin: Like we're always
saying, "Morning, Harry Gedges.

07:58.270 --> 07:59.409
How you doing,
Harry Gedges?

07:59.444 --> 08:00.687
Happy Birthday,
Harry Gedges."

08:00.721 --> 08:02.309
-Stop saying it!
-Why, Harry Gedges?

08:02.343 --> 08:03.655
That's not the name
I've been using!

08:03.690 --> 08:04.898
What do you mean,
Harry Gedges?

08:04.932 --> 08:06.416
I've been living
under a pseudonym

08:06.451 --> 08:07.694
for the last 20 years!

08:07.728 --> 08:08.971
Looks more like a fedora,
Harry Gedges!

08:09.005 --> 08:11.732
Not my hat.
A pseudonym is a fake name!

08:11.767 --> 08:13.907
It was given to me by the
Witness Protection people

08:13.941 --> 08:15.080
when they moved me to Elmore
for my own safety.

08:15.115 --> 08:16.806
Why, Harry Gedges?

08:16.841 --> 08:19.844
Harry: I testified in court
against some very bad people.

08:19.878 --> 08:21.984
And ever since then,
I've had to live

08:22.018 --> 08:24.607
under the fake name
that you know me by.

08:25.712 --> 08:27.541
Which is Mr...
B--

08:27.576 --> 08:30.924
No! We don't know your name,
all right?!

08:30.958 --> 08:32.442
Tell us what it is.

08:32.477 --> 08:33.754
Wait, you don't know my name?

08:33.789 --> 08:35.894
We've been neighbors
since you were born!

08:35.929 --> 08:38.103
If my life wasn't
in immediate danger,

08:38.138 --> 08:39.449
I'd be really hurt right now.

08:39.484 --> 08:41.659
Huh.
It's Gary Hedges.

08:41.693 --> 08:43.212
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

08:43.246 --> 08:45.455
I'm out of here.

08:45.490 --> 08:46.767
So let me
get this straight.

08:46.802 --> 08:48.389
Your real name
is Harry Gedges,

08:48.424 --> 08:49.839
and your fake name
is Gary Hedges?

08:49.874 --> 08:51.945
That's not
very imaginative.

08:51.979 --> 08:53.118
I didn't choose it!

08:53.153 --> 08:54.464
Okay.
There's no way

08:54.499 --> 08:56.570
those guys could have
followed us.

08:56.605 --> 08:58.503
Who, those guys?

09:00.574 --> 09:02.680
Dog: "Do you know this man?

09:02.714 --> 09:05.199
He lives at 1024 York Street.

09:05.234 --> 09:06.373
Here's a map.

09:06.407 --> 09:07.788
This is the house.

09:07.823 --> 09:09.031
If the front door is locked,

09:09.065 --> 09:10.722
there is a key
under the g-nome."

09:10.757 --> 09:12.862
How on earth did they find out
where I live?!

09:12.897 --> 09:14.450
-Uh, lucky guess?
-Lucky guess?

09:14.484 --> 09:15.624
Then I got no choice.

09:15.658 --> 09:17.142
I'm gonna have to skip town

09:17.177 --> 09:19.973
and leave behind my new life
and beautiful home.

09:20.007 --> 09:21.491
I think beautiful's
overselling it.

09:21.526 --> 09:22.562
Dude, not the time.

09:22.596 --> 09:24.633
Yeah, sorry.
Ha! I got it!

09:24.667 --> 09:27.221
You don't have to skip town
if they think you're --

09:27.256 --> 09:28.706
[ Imitates choking sound ]

09:28.740 --> 09:30.708
I don't think pretending
he's a duck is gonna help.

09:30.742 --> 09:32.226
No! They'll leave
if they think

09:32.261 --> 09:33.503
he's already
kicked the bucket.

09:33.538 --> 09:34.850
I know exactly
what to do.

09:36.334 --> 09:37.887
[ Growling ]

09:37.922 --> 09:40.510
[ Harry panting ]

09:42.202 --> 09:43.997
Genius!

09:44.031 --> 09:46.344
Oh, no!
-Hmm?

09:46.378 --> 09:50.486
I was just cleaning the windows,
and now I have lost my balance.

09:50.520 --> 09:53.627
I hope there is
no tragic consequence!

09:53.662 --> 09:57.769
[ Electricity buzzing ]

09:57.804 --> 09:58.977
[ Thud! ]

10:03.499 --> 10:05.432
[ Guns cocking ]

10:05.466 --> 10:07.330
[ Truck horn blows ]

10:07.365 --> 10:10.023
[ Thudding ]

10:10.057 --> 10:12.922
[ Clanking ]

10:12.957 --> 10:14.855
[ Thudding ]

10:21.379 --> 10:22.898
[ Thudding ]

10:27.834 --> 10:30.319
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

10:30.353 --> 10:33.218
[ Engine starts, brakes squeal ]

10:33.253 --> 10:36.463
[ Thudding ]

10:36.497 --> 10:37.706
Ha! It worked!

10:37.740 --> 10:39.293
Throwing that dummy
out of the window

10:39.328 --> 10:40.709
was a great idea.

10:40.743 --> 10:42.227
Now I get to keep my life
and my beautiful home.

10:42.262 --> 10:45.058
Yeah, it wasn't supposed
to fall out of the window.

10:45.092 --> 10:49.579
It was meant to look like you
were in the house when it --

10:49.614 --> 10:50.891
[ Explosion! ]

10:50.926 --> 10:52.030
Uhh, uhh.

10:52.065 --> 10:54.861
This might not be
the best time to ask,

10:54.895 --> 10:58.727
but would you rather we call you
Harry Gedges or Gary Hedges?

10:58.761 --> 11:00.901
I'd rather you never
talk to me again.
